@NODE MergeMega "Merge Index & Title"

Merge's two different Index & Title database file together to form one larger
database,

By Merge-ing your friends MegaCdPlayer database files you can save youself
a lot of typing.

Any Cd's that are allready in your database not be added.

@ENDNODE
@NODE SaveMega "Save Index & Title"

Save Index & Title database files, So you can Merge them with your mates.
@ENDNODE
@NODE MergeInterplay "Merge InterPlay List"

Merge Interplay list format file and convert to MegaCdPlayers format.

This menu command first converts the Interplay format to MegaCdPlayers
format and then save's the result files into Ram: then these files are
merged into the MegaCdPlayer's database files.

@ENDNODE
@NODE CheckMega "Check Index & Title"

This Check's MegaCdPlayers Index & Title files for any errors.

The Check's that are made are:

Index File Header
Index File size match match number of Cd's
Index File Cd's have <100 tracks
Title File Header

Along with a lot of other checks..
@ENDNODE

@Node ResetCurrent "Menu  Reset Current CD Played Count"
This will Reset the Current Cd Played Count that is keep by MegaCdPlayer
to Zero.

This is usefully if you wish to take out a Cd from the Top Ten Chart.
@Endnode

@Node ResetAll "Menu  Reset All CD's Played Counts"
This will Reset ALL Cd Played Counts records keep by MegaCdPlayer
to Zero.

This is usefully if you wish to start a new Top Ten Chart for scratch.


Note:  Once ResetALL is done you cannot recover the count records.
@Endnode


@Node CDTopTen "Menu CDTopTen"
This will show a Cd top ten chart of the most played CD's.

The Chart looks like this:

 1 - The Best of			45
 2 - The Rest of			34
 3 - The Most of			29
 4 - The others				24
 5 - The Best of the others		20
 6 - The Rest of the others		17
 7 - The Greatest Hits			14
 8 - The Worse of			11
 9 - All the crap by			 9
10 - Crap Crap Crap by			 3

Pos- Cd Title				Number of times Cd played

@Endnode

@NODE Hide "Menu Hide"

This will hide the normal full size window to a small Title bar at the top
right of the screen.

You can control the cd player with the small buttons on this Title bar,
the buttons are:

	@{"01" link "TrackNo"}	@{">" link "play"}	@{"O" link "stop"}	@{"||" link "pause"}	@{"<" link "track"}	@{">" link "track"}
	T	P	S	P	P  t	N  t
	R	 L	 T	 A 	 r  r	 e  r
 	A	  A	  O	  U	  e  a	  x  a
	C	   Y	   P	   S	   v  c	   t  c
	K			    E	    i  k       k
					     o
	No.				      u
	 				       s

If you click on the track number of the Hidden window title bar the window
will be go back to full size agian.
@ENDNODE

@Node Show "Menu  Show"
Show's the complete list of Cd's Titles stored in MegacdPlayers database files.

You browse through the list by moving the side Prop. Gadget

To see the Cd Title's Tracks names click the mouse on the required Cd Title
the Track names will then be show in place of Cd Titles.

To return to Cd Title display mode, Just click mouse on any Cd Track name.


The Cd Titles mode displays the number of tracks, cd Title followed by
the number of times played count.

Example:

Trks  --- CD Title ---					PlayedCount
  10 RE:Mix Cd No.12  July 1995					8 


The@{" SaveGuide " Link SaveGuide}Button


Note. show takes about 2 seconds to sort 300 cd titles
@Endnode

@Node SaveGuide "Show SaveGuide Button"
The SaveGuide Button will save a complete list of Cd's Titles stored
in MegacdPlayers database files in the Amiga Guide format.

Note. Old Version MegaCdplayer user's Make sure you have copyied the GuideIcon
      to the DataStore Directory, Else a Icon will not be saved with Guide.
@EndNode

@NODE About "Menu  About"

The About will give you the info and also the current Cd in drive's 
play time and how many times that cd has been played
and the Total number of cd's played to date with this player.
@ENDNODE

@NODE Quit "Menu  Quit Cd Player"

This is to Exit the Cd Player and stop playing if currently is.
@ENDNODE


@NODE EditOnOff "Menu  Edit Mode On/Off"

Edit On mode
------------
Any changes made to the current Cd's text are saved to the
MegaCdPlayers data base "Title" file,
 
Note:	Saves are Only made when the Return key is pressed on Cd title
	or Track names.

	The track name display will not be updated or Track selection
	enabled when a track ends or when you click on a new track,
	This has been done to make editing easyer when playing a Cd,
	and stop the Cd jumping to the track your editing, you can
	still use @{"< TRACK > " link "track"} to select a track.


Edit Off mode 
-------------
Saving on edit's is turned off, Track Update & Selection turn back on.
@ENDNODE



@NODE "Prefs" "Menu  Preferences window"


 			@{" Move CD Buttons " link "MoveCdButtons"}


@{"  " link "prefstick"} @{" Play Cd when Inserted" link "Prefs1"}		@{"  " link "prefstick"} @{"Continuous Play Mode" link "PrefContPlay"}
@{"  " link "prefstick"} @{" Negative Values Cd Timer" link "Prefs2"}
