@node TrackProp "Current Track Position Slider"

This Show's the current position of Cd track by the position of the slider,

You can move this Slider and select a new part of the current Cd track 
to continue playing from, at any time while playing.

@endnode

@node TrackNo "shows current track"

	Show's the current Track Number playing.
@endnode

@node tracktime "Play time of track"

 At the end of each cd track's name is the track's play time  00:00
						 	      ^^ ^^
					   	Minutes 00-99 ^^ ^^
					   			 ^^Seconds 00-59
@endnode

@node Title "The Cd's Title Name"

Current Cd's Title Name, Click on Cd's title to Edit.

@{" See Edit On Off " link "EditOnOff"}
@endnode

@node ttrack "Track Number"

	This is the Track number.
@endnode

@node Cdtrackname "Track Name"

Cd's track Name,  Click on the tracks name to Edit.

@{"See Edit On Off " link "EditOnOff"}
@endnode


@node Search "Search back and forth"

@{b}	<< SEARCH >>
	============
@{ub}
	This function is used to FastBackward/FastForward the CD.  Search
	is  used  when  you  want to skip to one part of a track.  If you
	don't  like  the beginning of a track, you simply search thru the
	track  using  <<  or  >> until you reach the part you like.
	Search-speed  is  about  30 times faster than normal playing-time.
@endnode


@node Preview "Preview 10 seconds of each track" 

@{b}	Preview
	=======
@{ub}
	The preview function will browse thru all Cd tracks playing
	each track for 10 seconds.
	To disable this function, just press Play or Stop.
@endnode

@node track "Previous/Next Cd Track"

@{b}	< TRACK >
	=========
@{ub}
	Steps the Cd player to '<' Previous or Next '>'  Cd track.
	When in program mode steps program number.
@endnode


@node pause "Pauses the current track"

@{b}	Pause
	=====
@{ub}
	Pauses the CD player.  By pressing the Pause (or Play) button,
	the CD will continue playing from where it was paused.
@endnode


@node Stop "Stop Cd playing"

@{b}	Stop
	====
@{ub}
	Stop will cause the CD to stop playing.

	Stop will also cancel's Pause if on.

	Also if you press Stop button twice the Cd player will stop the Cd
	Motor spinning round.  Play will start it again if you so wish.
@endnode

@node play "Play track"

@{b}	Play
	====
@{ub}
	When pressed will start playing the selected Audio track or Play
	the program track number.   Play will also un-Pause the player
	if in the paused mode.
@endnode

@node loop "Loop functions"

@{b}	Loop functions
	==============
@{ub}
	There are three different loop-modes. These are as follows:


	No Loop : Turn Loop mode off.

	Loop    : Loop the current track playing over and over again.

	Loop CD : Loops the complete cd when at last track or last programed
		  track.

@endnode

@node speed "Change Cd play Speed"
@{b}	Speed
	=====
@{ub}
	Speed will toggle the cd players play speed between Normal Speed
	and Double Speed (X2 Speed).

	You can use Speed at anytime even when playing, but it will take
	a little time to change Speed.

	The Speed button will change to 'X2 SPEED' when at Double speed.
@endnode

@node Eject "Eject Cd"
@{b}	Eject		(Not Cd32)
	=====
@{ub}
	This button will open/close the cd draw on your cd drive.
@endnode


@node TrackSlider "slider is used to choose a track quickly"

@{b}	Track Slider
	============
@{ub}
	Used to select a track when there is a lot of tracks on a Cd.

	The  cd  track  name will be scrolled up or down when you use the
	slider.

	there  is also a  @{"Up" link "TrackSliderup"} & @{"Down" link "TrackSliderdown"} arrow gadgets.
@endnode

@node TrackSliderup "slider Arrow Up a track"

	The the Up arrow gadget will step Up one cd track name.
@endnode

@node TrackSliderdown "slider Arrow Down a track"

	The Down arrow gadget will step Down one cd track name.
@endnode

@node timer "Time Mode"

@{b}	Cd Timer
	========
@{ub}
	The play timer displays minutes and seconds of cd time played 
	depending on Timer mode set.	See @{" TimerMode " link "timermode"}

		 00:00
		  |  |___: Seconds 00-59
		  |______: Minutes 00-99

Note: If the MegaCdPlayer's window is not currently selected the timer will
      not be updated.
@endnode


@node TimerMode  "Toggles how to show time on the Cd Timer"

@{b}	TimeMode
	========
@{ub}
	Toggles play Timer mode.  There are four modes as follows:

	- Track Elapsed		Time Cd Track has played
	- Track Remainder	Time left to play of Cd Track
	- CD Elapsed		Total Time Cd has played
	- CD Remainder		Total Time left to play of Cd
@endnode


@node Program "Opens the Programing window"
@{b}		Program
		=======
@{ub}	With  Program  you  can  program the order you wish the player to
	play  the  Cd  tracks  in and what tracks you wish to play.  When
	Program  is selected a program window is open you can then select
	the  tracks  you  wish to play by clicking on them as normal, the
	track  numbers  selected  will  appear in the program window in a
	sequence of boxs at the current cursor postion (white box).

	Note you can insert track numbers by clicking on the box you wish
	to Insert to.

	Buttons in Program window:

  @{"2" link b}@{"6" link b}@{"3" link b}@{"4" link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}	@{" Delete " link "ProgDelete"}	@{" Random " link "prograndom"} 
  @{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}	@{" Clear " link "ProgClear"}		@{" Seq Up " link "ProgSeqUp"}
  @{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}			@{" Seq Down " link "ProgSeqDown"}
  @{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}	@{" Load " link "ProgLoad"}	@{" Save " link "ProgSave"}
  @{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}@{" " link b}
						@{" Cancel " link "ProgCancel"}  @{" Done " link "ProgDone"}
@endnode

@NODE b "Program Box track numbers"

These show you the track number of in the program sequence selected.

You can insert track numbers by clicking on theses box's you wish to Insert to.

The white box is the current cursor position. 
@endnode

@NODE ProgDone

Click on Done when you have finished programming (or Close Program window).
@endnode

@NODE ProgCancel

Click on Cancel if you want to cancel program mode. (Ie Turn it Off)
@endnode

@NODE ProgDelete

Delete programmed track number at the current cursor postion. 
@endnode

@NODE ProgClear

Clear all Programmed track numbers.
@endnode

@node ProgRandom "Random"

@{b}	Random
	======
@{ub}
	Random  will  pick a randomly selected sequence of tracks and put
	them  in  the  program  box numbers, Or if you have selected some
	tracks  in the program box numbers Random will put those you have
	allready selected in a Random order.
@endnode

@node ProgSeqUp "Program Button Sequence"

@{b}	Seq Up
	======
@{ub}
	Seq Up will place a sequence of Cd tracks Starting with 1st Audio
	track  to  Last  track  and  put  them in the program box numbers.
	Will place them at the end of any you may have allready picked.
@endnode

@node ProgSeqDown "Program Button Sequence"

@{b}	Seq Down
	========
@{ub}
	Seq Down  will  place a sequence of Cd tracks Starting with Last
	Audio track to 1st track and put them in the program box numbers.
	Will place them at the end of any you may have allready picked.
@endnode

@node ProgSave "Program Button Save"

@{b}	Save
	====
@{ub}
	Save a program sequence for the current Cd in the drive.

	This sequence will be loaded and program mode switched on when
	a Cd is Inserted into Cd drive If the "Auto Program Mode Cd Inserted"
	is on in the prefs.
@endnode

@node ProgLoad "Program Button Load"

@{b}	Load
	====
@{ub}
	Load a program sequence for the current Cd in the drive.

Note: Only will Load if one has been saved, Else nothing will happen. 
@endnode

